EQT reported first quarter 2026 total production sales volumes of 618 Bcfe, compared with 571 Bcfe for the same period in 2025.
For the second quarter of 2026, EQT issued operating guidance for total sales volume of 570 Bcfe to 620 Bcfe and total liquids sales volume of 5,000 Mbbl to 5,350 Mbbl, including ethane sales of 1,650 Mbbl to 1,800 Mbbl.
For full year 2026, EQT guided to total sales volume of 2,275 Bcfe to 2,375 Bcfe and total liquids sales volume of 20,000 Mbbl to 21,200 Mbbl, with ethane sales of 6,500 Mbbl to 6,900 Mbbl.
EQT reported fourth quarter 2025 total sales volumes of 608,994 MMcfe and full year 2025 total sales volumes of 2,382,367 MMcfe. CEO Toby Rice co founded Energy Corps, a nonprofit focused on expanding energy infrastructure in developing countries, with support that includes a US$200,000 grant from the Rockefeller Foundation.
Fair value reset from US$65.96 to US$70.48 in the modeled valuation range.
Revenue growth assumption adjusted from 8.24% to 2.61% for projected dollar sales expansion.
Net profit margin updated from 34.77% to 34.04% on expected earnings per dollar of sales.
Future P/E multiple revised from 15.85x to 17.93x on forecast earnings.
Discount rate moved from 6.98% to 7.11% in the required return assumption.
